{
  "stem": "4189.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And since my brother was only at that time 12 years old, he-- another family had pity on us, and they took him in.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A family of better means who could afford to do this without being paid.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had no children, so they took him in, and they took care of him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I myself, I had to look for odd jobs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was not allowed-- officially, I was not allowed to work because the Belgium authority let us stay there as refugees.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They gave us what they call a permit that was good for three months.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But with that permit, you were not allowed to work, and every three months you had to go back to the police, you had to register, and they would renew that permit for another three months.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they did not really bother you, they would not send you back to Germany, but they kept watching you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I found some odd jobs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I found a job in a bakery, which was very good because at least I had bread to eat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This particular bakery, for instance, before the war, this was a very fancy bakery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They used to make cakes and they had a coffee shop.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But all this was gone now because during the war, they were only allowed to bake bread.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If they were caught to bake any other goods like rolls or challah or anything like that, that would be subject to heavy fines and maybe even closed up altogether.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we were only allowed to buy the official bread that was allowed to be sold with those food rations.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But it was a warm place, in the bakery it was warm.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
